reviews.text:
Saw some kids eating the candies and Chocolate from the storage boxes. See the picture I posted. A lot of time I unable to take picture while holding things.

I find it disgusting leh if some kid bite and throw back to the box.

Cashier was very rude! Rolled eyes and didn't select paywave as she selected UOB which didn't allow my google pay to go through. Had a plastic bag on my own and told her I didn't need more but was shown poor attitude. She was some indian cashier where I never had issue before, customer service is important please buckle up when we are spending money at your establishment.

The Giant branch at Pioneer Mall is spacious with its products spread across 2 levels of the mall.

Products are usually neatly placed, with quite a lot of enticing offers from time to time. Like most supermarket, you can find anything her, even toys and some electronics.

Service is fast and attitude of staff is decent. Food court is nearby if you are hungry.

Two-storey giant. Very big very spacious. Goods are well organized. Can find many household products & necessities around here.

Human side cashier is slightly slow. Highly reccomend using self-check out counter if possible. (Only accept card payments)

This giant also has the uncle jack cooked food store. Quite reasonably priced roast chicken & food products with decent taste.

Staff are generally quite productive & efficient in replacing all the goods & stocks and quite friendly to all customers.
Pioneer mall big shopping centre gaint shop wet market also groceries good chocolates biscuits
